"@misprintedtype @marcos_placona @firefox @googlechrome @slsoftworks Hey :) I think it's implementation level, although not entirely sure what the spec says regarding it. When a page goes idle (i.e. changing tabs), it seems that the SW script is re-excuted in Firefox when a message is passed to it, where as the SW seems to persist in Chrome"
"@misprintedtype @marcos_placona @firefox @googlechrome @slsoftworks Yes I can do, I will try and write it up coherently this evening. Thanks :)"
"@misprintedtype @marcos_placona @firefox @googlechrome @slsoftworks After some research, I think this is the same issue I'm seeing: https://t.co/oaM3xz66Ws"
